<p>Suburban areas like Dr. Phillips, Windermere, and Winter Park feature larger homes with ample roof space ideal for solar installations, though mature tree canopy may require strategic panel placement. These affluent neighborhoods often see the greatest return on investment from high-end HVAC systems with advanced features like whole-home air purification and smart home integration. Newer developments in areas like Lake Nona and Baldwin Park typically have modern electrical systems and energy-efficient construction that complement solar installations, while master-planned communities may have HOA restrictions requiring architectural approval for visible solar panels.</p>

